On June 1, 2019, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation expressing condolences for the victims of the shooting at the Virginia Beach Municipal Center in Virginia Beach, Virginia. The proclamation called for Americans to unite in prayer for the injured and the families and friends of the victims. As a mark of respect, the President ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at various locations, including the White House and all public buildings and military posts, until June 4, 2019. The proclamation was signed on June 1, 2019.